annoying.}  ) 26... fxg3 27. Rg1 $2 { The idea of taking on g3 with the rook is
simply bad.}  ( 27. hxg3 { this would have gone into a very long game, and
despite Grischuk's time trouble he might have been able to save the position.}
) 27... Kf8 28. Rxg3 Nc5 { The weakness of f4 will soon be felt.}  29. Bh3 Re8
$1 30. Rb1 Nh5 $1 31. Rg5 Nf4 { With the knights swarming the position, this is
clearly over. The fact that Grischuk has one minute and a few seconds to make
all the moves until the 40th did not help the situation.}  32. Bf1 Ra8 33. Bc4
Ra2 34. Rg4 Rh6 35. h4 Nfd3 36. Rg2 Rxh4+ 37. Kg1 Ra7 38. d6 Rh6 39. Rh2 Rxd6 
